:: Start
You wake up. The ceiling is familiar.

Today is the quarterly review. Your department presents to the board this afternoon — leadership, stakeholders, people whose names are on the building.

You have been preparing for three weeks. The work is good. You know it is good.

[[Get dressed]]


:: Get dressed
You stand in front of your closet.

What does today require of you?

[[Masculine formal — suit and tie]]
[[Masculine casual — slacks, open collar]]
[[Feminine formal — tailored suit, blouse]]
[[Feminine casual — dress, soft wear]]


:: Masculine formal — suit and tie
A dark suit. A tie you selected because it reads as serious without being aggressive. Dress shoes. Everything pressed.

You look at yourself in the mirror for a moment longer than necessary.

You look the part. You have always been told you look the part in this.

[[Eavesdrop — masc formal]]


:: Masculine casual — slacks, open collar
Dark slacks. A collared shirt, open at the neck. Clean. Put together but not formal. The kind of thing that reads as confident rather than trying.

You glance at yourself. Fine. Good, even.

You tell yourself it doesn't matter what you wear. You are half-convinced.

[[Eavesdrop — masc casual]]


:: Feminine formal — tailored suit, blouse
A tailored blazer and matching trousers. A blouse underneath, tasteful. Heels low enough to walk in. Everything deliberate.

You look at yourself. You look authoritative. You chose this because you wanted to be taken seriously today.

You wonder, briefly, if you will be.

[[Eavesdrop — fem formal]]


:: Feminine casual — dress, soft wear
A dress you like. Comfortable. The kind of thing that makes you feel like yourself on an ordinary day. You chose it because you have enough to think about today without your clothes adding to it.

You look in the mirror. You look like you. That used to feel like enough.

[[Eavesdrop — fem casual]]


:: Eavesdrop — masc formal
You are outside the meeting room. You can hear voices inside.

You should not eavesdrop. That would be unprofessional.

You pause. Did they just say your name?

---

Coworker A: "Wow — you can really tell this presentation is a big deal just by the outfit."

Coworker B: "I know, right? I've never seen them so put together."

Coworker A: "They should just dress like that every day."

*Laughter.*

---

//You step back from the door. They weren't saying anything wrong. That's the part that stays with you — they were complimenting you, and somehow it still felt like being measured.//

[[Presentation intro — masc formal]]


