:: Boss meeting — masc formal praised
Boss: "Close the door."

"Great work today. I mean it. The board was impressed — Okonkwo mentioned you specifically on the way out."

"That's the kind of thing I want to see more of. Confidence. Owning the room. You've got good instincts — I want you using them."

"Keep doing what you're doing."

---

//Reflection: You were confident and it was called leadership. You corrected someone and it was called competence. You spoke over your manager and it was called initiative. The institution has a word for all of these things when you do them. You leave his office and you think about the one colleague whose confidence gets a different word entirely. You think about that for a long time.//

//Butler, Judith. Gender Trouble: "Gender is a kind of imitation for which there is no original." The praise you received today rewarded a performance — not the work, but the gendered performance of authority that surrounded it. You did not invent this script. You inherited it.//

[[End — replay?]]


